      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:23:6",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " كَثْرَةُ الضَّحِكِ تُمِيتُ الْقَلْبَ ",
        "وَ قَالَ كَثْرَةُ الضَّحِكِ تَمِيثُ الدِّينَ كَمَا يَمِيثُ الْمَاءُ الْمِلْحَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Mansour, from Hareyz, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Abundant laughter deadens the heart’. ",
          "And he<sup style=\"font-weight: normal\">asws</sup> said: ‘Abundant laughter dissolves the Religion just as the water dissolves the salt’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Mansur from Hariz from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “Much laughing deadens the heart. He has also said, ‘Much laughing melts one’s religion just as water melts salt.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
